---
// /waitlist: the calm "you are on the list" confirmation for a signup that is
// pending allowlist approval. The hosted console is opening in gated waves; this
// page is the friendly landing when access is not granted yet, and the console's
// own waitlisted state can also link here. No dead end: run the open engine now,
// or head back home. noindex (thin, transactional). Never use em or en dashes.
import Site from '../layouts/Site.astro';

const DOCS = '/docs/quickstart';
const TITLE = 'You are on the Mitos waitlist';
const DESC =
  'Your spot is saved. The hosted console opens in waves and we will email you when your access is ready. Run the open-source engine today while you wait.';
---

<Site title={TITLE} description={DESC} noindex={true}>
  <section class="hero container">
    <div class="hero-aura" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-in reveal">
      <h1>You are on the list.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Thanks for signing up. We are opening the hosted console in waves, and we
        will email you the moment your access is ready. There is nothing else you
        need to do.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href={DOCS}>Run the open engine now</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost btn-lg" href="/">Back to home</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <div class="intro">
    <p>
      Mitos is open source under Apache 2.0, so you do not have to wait to try the
      real thing. Follow the <a href="/docs/quickstart">quickstart</a> to fork a
      running microVM into a swarm on your own machine or cluster today. When your
      hosted access opens, the same workflow moves to the managed console with your
      free starting credit already in place.
    </p>
    <p>
      We approve in waves to keep the early experience solid. Your place is saved
      against the email you signed up with, so keep an eye on your inbox. If you
      think you should already have access, reach us on
      <a href="https://github.com/mitos-run/mitos/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
    </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Site>

<style>
  .hero { padding-block: 184px 0; position: relative; }
  .hero-aura { position: absolute; top: -60px; left: 4%; width: 680px; max-width: 90vw; height: 520px; z-index: 0; pointer-events: none;
    background: radial-gradient(closest-side, color-mix(in srgb, var(--magenta) 11%, transparent), transparent 72%);
    opacity: .5; filter: blur(8px); }
  .hero-in { position: relative; z-index: 1; max-width: 720px; }
  .hero h1 { font-size: var(--text-display); line-height: 1.0; letter-spacing: -.035em; font-weight: 400; margin: 0 0 20px; }
  .lede { font-size: var(--text-lede); color: var(--ink-2); max-width: 34em; margin: 0 0 28px; line-height: 1.5; }
  .hero-actions { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .intro { max-width: 52em; padding-top: 56px; padding-bottom: 96px; }
  .intro p { color: var(--ink-2); font-size: var(--text-body); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 20px; }
  .intro a { color: var(--cyan); border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--cyan) 30%, transparent); }
  .intro a:hover { border-bottom-color: var(--cyan); }
  @media (max-width: 760px) { .hero { padding-block: 104px 0; } .hero h1 { font-size: var(--text-display-sm); line-height: 1.06; } }
</style>
